
Overview of adj portentous

The adj portentous has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) portentous, prodigious -- (of momentous or ominous significance; "such a portentous...monster raised all my curiosity"- Herman Melville; "a prodigious vision")
2. (1) fateful, foreboding, portentous -- (ominously prophetic)
3. grandiloquent, overblown, pompous, pontifical, portentous -- (puffed up with vanity; "a grandiloquent and boastful manner"; "overblown oratory"; "a pompous speech"; "pseudo-scientific gobbledygook and pontifical hooey"- Newsweek)
